64 Q_EXPORT intptr_t vmMain(intptr_t command, intptr_t arg0, intptr_t arg1, intptr_t arg2, intptr_t arg3, intptr_t arg4, intptr_t arg5, intptr_t arg6, intptr_t arg7, intptr_t arg8, intptr_t arg9, intptr_t arg10, intptr_t arg11)
65 {
66  switch (command)
67  {
68  case CG_INIT:
69  CG_Init(arg0, arg1, arg2, (qboolean)arg3, arg4, (demoPlayInfo_t *)arg5, arg6);
70  cgs.initing = qfalse;
71  return 0;
72  case CG_SHUTDOWN:
73  CG_Shutdown();
74  return 0;
75  case CG_CONSOLE_COMMAND:
76  return CG_ConsoleCommand();
77  case CG_DRAW_ACTIVE_FRAME:
78  CG_DrawActiveFrame(arg0, (qboolean)arg2); // arg1 removed, order kept for vanilla client compatibility
79  return 0;
80  case CG_CROSSHAIR_PLAYER:
81  return CG_CrosshairPlayer();
82  case CG_LAST_ATTACKER:
83  return CG_LastAttacker();
84  case CG_KEY_EVENT:
85  CG_KeyEvent(arg0, (qboolean)arg1);
86  return 0;
87  case CG_MOUSE_EVENT:
88  cgDC.cursorx = cgs.cursorX;
89  cgDC.cursory = cgs.cursorY;
90  // when the limbopanel is open, we want the cursor to be able to move all the way to the right edge of the screen..
91  // ... same for the debriefing screen
92  if (cg.showGameView || cgs.dbShowing)
93  {
94  if (!Ccg_Is43Screen())
95  {
96  cgDC.cursorx *= cgs.adr43;
97  }
98  }
99  CG_MouseEvent(arg0, arg1);
100  return 0;
101  case CG_EVENT_HANDLING:
102  CG_EventHandling(arg0, qtrue);
103  return 0;
104  case CG_GET_TAG:
105  return CG_GetTag(arg0, (char *)arg1, (orientation_t *)arg2);
106  case CG_CHECKEXECKEY:
107  return CG_CheckExecKey(arg0);
108  case CG_WANTSBINDKEYS:
109  return (g_waitingForKey && g_bindItem) ? qtrue : qfalse;
110  case CG_MESSAGERECEIVED:
111  return -1;
112  default:
113  CG_Error("vmMain: unknown command %li", (long)command);
114  break;
115  }
116  return -1;
117 }

609 void CG_RegisterCvars(void)
610 {
611  unsigned int i;
612  cvarTable_t *cv;
613  char var[MAX_TOKEN_CHARS];
614 
615  CG_Printf("%d client cvars in use\n", cvarTableSize);
616 
617  trap_Cvar_Set("cg_letterbox", "0"); // force this for people who might have it in their cfg
618 
619  for (i = 0, cv = cvarTable ; i < cvarTableSize ; i++, cv++)
620  {
621  trap_Cvar_Register(cv->vmCvar, cv->cvarName, cv->defaultString, cv->cvarFlags);
622  if (cv->vmCvar != NULL)
623  {
624  // force the update to range check this cvar on first run
625  if (cv->vmCvar == &cg_errorDecay)
626  {
627  cv->modificationCount = !cv->vmCvar->modificationCount;
628  }
629  else
630  {
631  cv->modificationCount = cv->vmCvar->modificationCount;
632  }
633  }
634  }
635 
636  // see if we are also running the server on this machine
637  trap_Cvar_VariableStringBuffer("sv_running", var, sizeof(var));
638  cgs.localServer = (qboolean)(atoi(var));
639 
640  // um, here, why?
641  CG_setClientFlags();
642  BG_setCrosshair(cg_crosshairColor.string, cg.xhairColor, cg_crosshairAlpha.value, "cg_crosshairColor");
643  BG_setCrosshair(cg_crosshairColorAlt.string, cg.xhairColorAlt, cg_crosshairAlphaAlt.value, "cg_crosshairColorAlt");
644 
645  cvarsLoaded = qtrue;
646 }
647 
651 void CG_UpdateCvars(void)
652 {
653  unsigned int i;
654  qboolean fSetFlags = qfalse;
655  cvarTable_t *cv;
656 
657  if (!cvarsLoaded)
658  {
659  return;
660  }
661 
662  for (i = 0, cv = cvarTable ; i < cvarTableSize ; i++, cv++)
663  {
664  if (cv->vmCvar)
665  {
666  trap_Cvar_Update(cv->vmCvar);
667  if (cv->modificationCount != cv->vmCvar->modificationCount)
668  {
669  cv->modificationCount = cv->vmCvar->modificationCount;
670 
671  // Check if we need to update any client flags to be sent to the server
672  if (cv->vmCvar == &cg_autoAction || cv->vmCvar == &cg_autoReload ||
673  cv->vmCvar == &int_cl_timenudge || cv->vmCvar == &int_cl_maxpackets ||
674  cv->vmCvar == &cg_autoactivate || cv->vmCvar == &cg_predictItems)
675  {
676  fSetFlags = qtrue;
677  }
678  else if (cv->vmCvar == &cg_crosshairColor || cv->vmCvar == &cg_crosshairAlpha)
679  {
680  BG_setCrosshair(cg_crosshairColor.string, cg.xhairColor, cg_crosshairAlpha.value, "cg_crosshairColor");
681  }
682  else if (cv->vmCvar == &cg_crosshairColorAlt || cv->vmCvar == &cg_crosshairAlphaAlt)
683  {
684  BG_setCrosshair(cg_crosshairColorAlt.string, cg.xhairColorAlt, cg_crosshairAlphaAlt.value, "cg_crosshairColorAlt");
685  }
686  else if (cv->vmCvar == &cg_rconPassword && *cg_rconPassword.string)
687  {
688  trap_SendConsoleCommand(va("rconAuth %s", cg_rconPassword.string));
689  }
690  else if (cv->vmCvar == &cg_refereePassword && *cg_refereePassword.string)
691  {
692  trap_SendConsoleCommand(va("ref %s", cg_refereePassword.string));
693  }
694  else if (cv->vmCvar == &demo_infoWindow)
695  {
696  if (demo_infoWindow.integer == 0 && cg.demohelpWindow == SHOW_ON)
697  {
698  CG_ShowHelp_On(&cg.demohelpWindow);
699  }
700  else if (demo_infoWindow.integer > 0 && cg.demohelpWindow != SHOW_ON)
701  {
702  CG_ShowHelp_On(&cg.demohelpWindow);
703  }
704  }
705  else if (cv->vmCvar == &cg_errorDecay)
706  {
707  // cap errordecay because
708  // prediction is EXTREMELY broken
709  // right now.
710  if (cg_errorDecay.value < 0.0f)
711  {
712  trap_Cvar_Set("cg_errorDecay", "0");
713  }
714  else if (cg_errorDecay.value > 500.0f)
715  {
716  trap_Cvar_Set("cg_errorDecay", "500");
717  }
718  }
719  }
720  }
721  }
722 
723  // Send any relevent updates
724  if (fSetFlags)
725  {
726  CG_setClientFlags();
727  }
728 }

997 int CG_cleanName(const char *pszIn, char *pszOut, int dwMaxLength, qboolean fCRLF)
998 {
999  const char *pInCopy = pszIn;
1000  const char *pszOutStart = pszOut;
1001 
1002  while (*pInCopy && (pszOut - pszOutStart < dwMaxLength - 1))
1003  {
1004  if (*pInCopy == '^')
1005  {
1006  pInCopy += ((pInCopy[1] == 0) ? 1 : 2);
1007  }
1008  else if ((*pInCopy < 32 && (!fCRLF || *pInCopy != '\n')) || (*pInCopy > 126))
1009  {
1010  pInCopy++;
1011  }
1012  else
1013  {
1014  *pszOut++ = *pInCopy++;
1015  }
1016  }
1017 
1018  *pszOut = 0;
1019  return(pszOut - pszOutStart);
1020 }

1027 int CG_findClientNum(const char *s)
1028 {
1029  int id;
1030  char s2[64], n2[64];
1031  qboolean fIsNumber = qtrue;
1032 
1033  // See if its a number or string
1034  for (id = 0; id < (int)strlen(s) && s[id] != 0; id++)
1035  {
1036  if (s[id] < '0' || s[id] > '9')
1037  {
1038  fIsNumber = qfalse;
1039  break;
1040  }
1041  }
1042 
1043  // numeric values are just slot numbers
1044  if (fIsNumber)
1045  {
1046  id = atoi(s);
1047  if (id >= 0 && id < cgs.maxclients && cgs.clientinfo[id].infoValid)
1048  {
1049  return(id);
1050  }
1051  }
1052 
1053  // check for a name match
1054  CG_cleanName(s, s2, sizeof(s2), qfalse);
1055  for (id = 0; id < cgs.maxclients; id++)
1056  {
1057  if (!cgs.clientinfo[id].infoValid)
1058  {
1059  continue;
1060  }
1061 
1062  CG_cleanName(cgs.clientinfo[id].name, n2, sizeof(n2), qfalse);
1063  if (!Q_stricmp(n2, s2))
1064  {
1065  return(id);
1066  }
1067  }
1068 
1069  CG_Printf("[cgnotify]%s ^3%s^7 %s.\n", CG_TranslateString("User"), s, CG_TranslateString("is not on the server"));
1070  return(-1);
1071 }

1085 void CG_LoadObjectiveData(void)
1086 {
1087  pc_token_t token, token2;
1088  int handle;
1089 
1090  if (cg_gameType.integer == GT_WOLF_LMS)
1091  {
1092  handle = trap_PC_LoadSource(va("maps/%s_lms.objdata", Q_strlwr(cgs.rawmapname)));
1093  }
1094  else
1095  {
1096  handle = trap_PC_LoadSource(va("maps/%s.objdata", Q_strlwr(cgs.rawmapname)));
1097  }
1098 
1099  if (!handle)
1100  {
1101  return;
1102  }
1103 
1104  while (1)
1105  {
1106  if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
1107  {
1108  break;
1109  }
1110 
1111  if (!Q_stricmp(token.string, "wm_mapdescription"))
1112  {
1113  if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
1114  {
1115  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : team parameter required\n");
1116  break;
1117  }
1118 
1119  if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token2))
1120  {
1121  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : description parameter required\n");
1122  break;
1123  }
1124 
1125  if (!Q_stricmp(token.string, "axis"))
1126  {
1127  Q_strncpyz(cg.objMapDescription_Axis, token2.string, sizeof(cg.objMapDescription_Axis));
1128  }
1129  else if (!Q_stricmp(token.string, "allied"))
1130  {
1131  Q_strncpyz(cg.objMapDescription_Allied, token2.string, sizeof(cg.objMapDescription_Allied));
1132  }
1133  else if (!Q_stricmp(token.string, "neutral"))
1134  {
1135  Q_strncpyz(cg.objMapDescription_Neutral, token2.string, sizeof(cg.objMapDescription_Neutral));
1136  }
1137  }
1138  else if (!Q_stricmp(token.string, "wm_objective_axis_desc"))
1139  {
1140  int i;
1141 
1142  if (!PC_Int_Parse(handle, &i))
1143  {
1144  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : number parameter required\n");
1145  break;
1146  }
1147 
1148  if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
1149  {
1150  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : description parameter required\n");
1151  break;
1152  }
1153 
1154  i--;
1155 
1156  if (i < 0 || i >= MAX_OBJECTIVES)
1157  {
1158  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : invalid objective number\n");
1159  break;
1160  }
1161 
1162  Q_strncpyz(cg.objDescription_Axis[i], token.string, sizeof(cg.objDescription_Axis[i]));
1163  }
1164  else if (!Q_stricmp(token.string, "wm_objective_allied_desc"))
1165  {
1166  int i;
1167 
1168  if (!PC_Int_Parse(handle, &i))
1169  {
1170  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : number parameter required\n");
1171  break;
1172  }
1173 
1174  if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
1175  {
1176  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : description parameter required\n");
1177  break;
1178  }
1179 
1180  i--;
1181 
1182  if (i < 0 || i >= MAX_OBJECTIVES)
1183  {
1184  CG_Printf("^1ERROR: bad objdata line : invalid objective number\n");
1185  break;
1186  }
1187 
1188  Q_strncpyz(cg.objDescription_Allied[i], token.string, sizeof(cg.objDescription_Allied[i]));
1189  }
1190  }
1191 
1192  trap_PC_FreeSource(handle);
1193 }

1200 void CG_SetupDlightstyles(void)
1201 {
1202  int i, j;
1203  char *str;
1204  char *token;
1205  int entnum;
1206  centity_t *cent;
1207 
1208  cg.lightstylesInited = qtrue;
1209 
1210  for (i = 1; i < MAX_DLIGHT_CONFIGSTRINGS; i++)
1211  {
1212  str = (char *) CG_ConfigString(CS_DLIGHTS + i);
1213  if (!strlen(str))
1214  {
1215  break;
1216  }
1217 
1218  token = COM_Parse(&str); // ent num
1219  entnum = atoi(token);
1220  cent = &cg_entities[entnum];
1221 
1222  token = COM_Parse(&str); // stylestring
1223  Q_strncpyz(cent->dl_stylestring, token, strlen(token));
1224 
1225  token = COM_Parse(&str); // offset
1226  cent->dl_frame = atoi(token);
1227  cent->dl_oldframe = cent->dl_frame - 1;
1228  if (cent->dl_oldframe < 0)
1229  {
1230  cent->dl_oldframe = strlen(cent->dl_stylestring);
1231  }
1232 
1233  token = COM_Parse(&str); // sound id
1234  cent->dl_sound = atoi(token);
1235 
1236  token = COM_Parse(&str); // attenuation
1237  cent->dl_atten = atoi(token);
1238 
1239  for (j = 0; j < (int)strlen(cent->dl_stylestring); j++)
1240  {
1241 
1242  cent->dl_stylestring[j] += cent->dl_atten; // adjust character for attenuation/amplification
1243 
1244  // clamp result
1245  if (cent->dl_stylestring[j] < 'a')
1246  {
1247  cent->dl_stylestring[j] = 'a';
1248  }
1249  if (cent->dl_stylestring[j] > 'z')
1250  {
1251  cent->dl_stylestring[j] = 'z';
1252  }
1253  }
1254 
1255  cent->dl_backlerp = 0.0;
1256  cent->dl_time = cg.time;
1257  }
1258 }
